This .csproj file includes the following NuGet packages:
- `Microsoft.AspNetCore`: The core package for ASP.NET Core.
- `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Core`: The package for ASP.NET Core MVC.

For the provided C# code, here is the complete code snippet:

```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;

var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);
var app = builder.Build();

app.UseHttpsRedirection();

var products = new[]
{
    new { Id = 1, Name = "Product 1", Price = 10.99m },
    new { Id = 2, Name = "Product 2", Price = 9.99m },
    new { Id = 3, Name = "Product 3", Price = 12.99m },
};

app.MapGet("/products", () => Results.Ok(products));
app.MapGet("/products/{id}", (int id) =>
{
    var product = products.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Id == id);
    return product != null ? Results.Ok(product) : Results.NotFound();
});

app.Run();
```

The above code defines an ASP.NET Core Web API that exposes two endpoints: `/products` and `/products/{id}`. The `/products` endpoint returns a list of all products, while the `/products/{id}` endpoint returns a single product with the specified `id`. If the product is not found, it returns a 404 Not Found response.